race.comment: McEvoy-trained VIXENETTE (11) is third up and will be sharper returning to the turf. Raced favourite on the synthetic last time but got too far back. Has placed third up and has the blinkers on for the first time. Her metro form stacks right up for this. VADERLEE (5) has needed both runs this preparation and is much better suited back in grade off the latest. Maps well and has plenty in the tank. TEARS ARE FLOWING (4) is a lightly-raced improver who will use an inside barrier. Bates goes on and she deserves consideration. COUNT IDA (7) has been a model of consistency so far this campaign. Comes here off a Donald victory. Holds each way appeal.
